should be avoided. \n        You can learn more about how we evaluate them in our \n        <a href=\"/how-we-rate-online-casinos/\">TCS Rating Methodology</a>.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q7 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">What is the typical minimum deposit for U.S. players?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Most casinos accept $10\u2013$25 as a starting deposit.</p>\n      <p>\n        Many U.S.-friendly casinos allow minimum deposits in the $10\u2013$25 range for card, online banking or crypto payments. \n        Some high-roller offers may require larger initial deposits, while certain welcome packages unlock different tiers \n        of bonuses depending on how much you deposit. Our \n        <a href=\"/usa-casino-bonus/\">USA Casino Bonus Guide</a> explains how deposit size, bonus structure and long-term value \n        connect in practice.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q8 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">Which games are most popular among U.S. online casino players?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Slots lead the way, with live dealer and table games close behind.</p>\n      <p>\n        For most American players, <strong>online slots</strong> are the main attraction \u2014 thanks to simple gameplay,\n        large jackpots and wide compatibility with bonuses. Live dealer blackjack, roulette and game-show style titles\n        have also grown quickly, along with video poker and newer crash-style games at some offshore sites.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        If you want to understand RTP, volatility and how different slot types fit your risk tolerance, \n        see our <a href=\"/usa-online-slots-guide/\">USA Online Slots Guide 2025</a> for a full overview.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q9 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">Do U.S. players still need bonus codes in 2025?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Less often \u2014 most major bonuses now trigger automatically.</p>\n      <p>\n        On many U.S.-facing casino sites, welcome bonuses and common reload offers are applied automatically when you\n        register or deposit through a verified promotion link. Bonus codes are still used for specific deals \u2014 such as\n        limited-time promotions, VIP reloads or exclusive campaigns \u2014 but they are no longer required for every offer.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        Our <a href=\"/usa-casino-bonus/\">USA Casino Bonus Guide</a> clearly flags when a code is needed and when it isn\u2019t.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q10 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">Where can U.S. players get help if gambling becomes a problem?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Free, confidential support is available nationwide.</p>\n      <p>\n        If gambling stops feeling like entertainment, it\u2019s important to slow down or stop and reach out for help.\n        U.S. players can access support through:\n      </p>\n      <ul style=\"padding-left:18px; margin-top:4px;\">\n        <li>\n          <a href=\"https://www.ncpgambling.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n            National Council on Problem Gambling (NCPG)\n          </a> \u2014 national resources, information and help services.\n        </li>\n        <li>\n         